  "id": "166efa1c-6ddc-56cb-a884-ef1193e490a8",
  "slug": "how-to-make-beef-soft-tacos",
  "name": "Soft Beef Tacos (Carne Asada)",
  "recipe_type": null,
  "brief_description": "This soft beef tacos recipe makes use of carne asada. It is so tasty to the point that it will awaken your sleeping taste buds.",
  "cuisine": null,
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Combine all the marinade ingredients in a large mixing bowl then mix together."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Put-in the chopped steak and mix with the marinade. Marinate for at least 3 hours."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Make the salsa.Grill the salsa ingredients until the color turns light to medium brown.Remove the ingredients from the grill and set aside until the temperature goes down.Liquefy the salsa ingredients using a blender or food processor then set aside."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Combine chopped cilantro, lime juice and sliced onion in a bowl then mix. Set aside. This will be the topping."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Heat a skillet or frying pan then pour-in 4 tablespoons of olive oil."
    },
    {
      "position": 6,
      "text": "Put-in the marinated steak and fry until color turns brown while the texture remains tender. Note: While doing this process, the juices and marinade absorbed by the steak may come out. This is normal; all you need to do is to wait until the liquids evaporate. Stir once in a while until the liquid is gone and the steaks are fried."
    },
    {
      "position": 7,
      "text": "Turn off heat and transfer the cooked steak in a plate."
    },
    {
      "position": 8,
      "text": "Wrap the tortillas in paper towel and microwave for a minute."
    },
    {
      "position": 9,
      "text": "Place the tortillas in a plate then arrange the cooked steak over it."
    },
    {
      "position": 10,
      "text": "Top with the mixture of cilantro, onion, and lime juice. Spoon-in some salsa and sprinkle your favorite cheese."
    },
    {
      "position": 11,
      "text": "Serve. Share and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
  "servings": 6,
  "cooking_time_minutes": 10,
  "preparation_time_minutes": 60,
